# Looking at the smtp and trustcas and adoptionusagemetering suites ...
# Although they are disruptive, they appear to my eyes to bedisruptive to different parts of MAS with no impact on one another ... I think all three (each have about a 30 minute runtime) should be able to run in parallel ...
# - smtp: only test_smtpcfg is disruptive (deletes and recreates SMTPCfg multiple times, but I don't think that would impact the other two)
# - trustcas: changes Suite config and verifies using SCIM whether defult CAs are included (or not) in the truststore
# - adoptionusagemetering: honestly not even sure why this is disruptive at all, seems to just be checking data that's already in the system

